      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must directly map to the clinical endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the FDA-accepted surrogate for pump-induced blood damage and directly informs the predicate device comparison. The scalar damage accumulation model, parameterized using power-law coefficients from the hemolysis correlation literature, produces RH as the primary output. Direct clinical relevance is established."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
